Library of Congress.description: The Library of Congress is the research library that officially serves the United States Congress, but which is the de facto national library of the United States. It is the oldest federal cultural institution in the United States. Wikipedia

Andrew Bayne Memorial Library.label: Andrew Bayne Memorial Library

Family History Library.description: The Family History Library is a genealogical research facility in downtown Salt Lake City. The library is open to the public free of charge and is operated by FamilySearch, the genealogical arm of the The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. Wikipedia

Harvard University Library.label: Harvard University LibraryHarvard University
Harvard University Library.description: The Harvard Library system comprises about 73 libraries, with more than 18 million volumes. It is the oldest library system in the United States, the largest academic and the largest private library system in the world. Wikipedia

King Township Public Library.description: The King Township Public Library is a public library system that serves King Township, Ontario in Canada. It consists of four branches located in King City, Nobleton, Schomberg, and Ansnorveldt. Wikipedia

Milwaukee Public Library.label: Milwaukee Public Library

Newcastle University Library.label: Newcastle University Library
Newcastle University Library.description: Newcastle University Library is the main library service for students and staff at Newcastle University, UK. Wikipedia

Princeton University Library.label: Firestone Memorial Library

Radcliffe Science Library.label: Radcliffe Science Library

Seattle Public Library.label: Seattle Public Library

Stockholm Public Library.label: Stockholm Public Library

Warsaw University Library.description:

Wellcome Library.label: Wellcome Library
Wellcome Library.description: The Wellcome Library is founded on the collection formed by Sir Henry Wellcome, whose personal wealth allowed him to create one of the most ambitious collections of the twentieth century. Wikipedia

Library of the Russian Academy of Scienc.label: Library of the Russian Academy of Sciences
Library of the Russian Academy of Scienc.description: The Library of the Russian Academy of Sciences is a large state-owned Russian library based in Saint Petersburg on Vasilievsky Island and open to employees of institutions of the Russian Academy of Sciences and scholars with higher education. Wikipedia

Russian State Library.label: Russian State Library
Russian State Library.description: The Russian State Library is the national library of Russia, located in Moscow. It is the largest in the country and the fourth largest in the world for its collection of books. It was named the V. I. Wikipedia

Benton Harbor Public Library.label: Benton Harbor Public Library

National Library of Russia.label: National Library of Russia

Calais Free Library.label: Calais Free Library

Walker Memorial Library.label: Walker Memorial Library

Alpena County Library.label: Alpena County Library
Alpena County Library.description: Alpena County Library is a public library in Alpena, Michigan, United States. Wikipedia

National Library of Kuwait.label: National Library of Kuwait

Biblioteca Nacional de Portugal.label: Biblioteca Nacional de Portugal

Austrian National Library.label: Austrian National Library

Halifax Public Libraries.label: Halifax Public Libraries

The University of Michigan Library is the university library system of the University of Michigan, based in Ann Arbor, Michigan, in the United States.

Zentralbibliothek der TU und UdK Berlin.label: Zentralbibliothek der TU und UdK Berlin

Owatonna Public Library.label: Owatonna Public Library
